dc_description_s: This data layer represents land use for Winnebago County, Wisconsin in 2010. It is a feature class within the geodatabase 'Winnebago_LandUse_2010.gdb'. [This data is updated from December 2012 to March of 2013. Land use is a very important aspect of a county, especially when it comes to planning for future and current projects. For Winnebago County there are 10 broad categories that land use can fall within. Land use also falls under sub categories, which can be found in the reference booklet or the attribute table of this data. The 10 broad categories are as follows: Agriculture, Other Open Land, Water, Woodlands, Residential, Commercial, Industrial, Utility, Institutional, and Recreational. The full description on how these categories are assigned to a specific land use can be found in the reference booklet.]
uw_supplemental_s: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements.
